size=1> Strongboww's Guide to Raiding as a &quot;upper level guild&quot;<br>
<br>
This is a multiple step process:<br>
<br>
1. Ranger's/Monks/Rogues are the typical scouts (bards and druids can fill this role as well) depending on whether the mob is trackable or not (won't get into a list of which ones are and from where). So we see Ubermob_01 is up. We announce to guild.<br>
<br>
2. Guild makes a decision based off numbers on line, needed classes (usually clerics and chanters make or break this decision process) A channel is normally started to do a headcount on who can come, needs flags, ect. ect.<br>
<br>
insert first &quot;patience time&quot; - 15 mins. - 1 hr.+ waiting for those needed or enough to get numbers up (add another 15+ to PoP targets with 15% rule for unflagged)<br>
<br>
3. Guild calls rally with 10 people still short to actually be able to accomplish kill<br>
<br>
insert more &quot;patience time&quot; equal to the amount of time it takes for those who were grinding out that last 15% of aaxp/xp to realize they can actually make it; those who didn't think we were gonna actually hit target and other random variables that have people slowly milling into raid<br>
<br>
this is that point where you'll here about what other guilds are moving towards zone, target ect. (Usually this is a case of someone trying to motivate people to hurry, paranoia - or your about to lose your target to a guild that will walk over you to kill it, YMMV)<br>
<br>
insert more &quot;patience time&quot; to calm down those who are freaking out about guild_04s location, ect.<br>
<br>
insert more &quot;patience time&quot; to deal with those who start to discuss possibly killing loot mobs, ssra mobs, whathaveyou and get them back on track to target at hand<br>
<br>
(hint - you'll be seeing a lot of patience time on raids)<br>
<br>
4. Clear mobs back to area of ubermob_01. <br>
<br>
insert more &quot;patient time&quot; = Deal with number of dead to summons, enrage, broken mez's<br>
<br>
5. Start up ghetto CoH or, if your really luck, CoH cycle=more patience time. This is when all those people who milled in start to make it.<br>
<br>
6. Start prep i.e. buffing, organizing last minute adjustments to groups ect. i.e. more patience time<br>
<br>
7.Restart CoH cycle for those who just logged on with the statement &quot;what's going on in uberzone_07?&quot; &quot;Am I too late?&quot;<br>
<br>
8. Rebuff from all those wonderful short term buffs<br>
<br>
9.Deal with respawn prior to attacking Ubermob_01<br>
<br>
10. Redo rez's and buffs of those who died to enrage, ect.<br>
<br>
11. Do finally &quot;So who is AFK?&quot;<br>
<br>
Insert &quot;patience time&quot; for those who were afk taking a shower, making dinner or sleeping without letting anybody know&quot;<br>
<br>
12. Engage mob<br>
<br>
13. Rez and rebuff more patience time<br>
<br>
14. Discuss with guild how we've gotten a little overconfident and laugh<br>
<br>
15. Re-engage mob<br>
<br>
16. Rapid rez of those who need flags =- RL also should announce loot drops, ect. at this point.<br>
<br>
insert more patience time = guild decides loot (your system varies here, not gonna get specific)<br>
<br>
17. 30 seconds before corpse rots, all loot is finally figured out and people rush to loot<br>
<br>
18. 20 mins. of gratz in guild/raid and tells commences.<br>
<br>
19. AoE TLs to bind commence.<br>
<br>
20. 5 people who were AFK when AoE TLs were announced come back to full spawn and death.<br>
<br>
21 5 people (usually a monk and cleric min.) go back and drag rez those AFKers.<br>
<br>
22. Guild starts to discuss that ubermob_25 is up and uncontested, maybe we should hit it, it's only 2 a.m., this should be quick(TM).<br>
<br>
Good theories in all honesty:<br>
<br>
Don't go on a raid unless you have the time + 1 hour to attend.<br>
Don't expect experience (actually expect to lose between 1-5%, level buffering is a good idea if you just dinged and know your gonna raid in the next 24-48 hours.)<br>
Loot probably won't go to you. Don't expect it - it's nothing personal, just the mob only drops 1 item normally and the other 15 people that can use it will be competing with you for that upgrade. If it's an upgrade - put in for it through whatever system your guild uses.<br>
Have fun. If your not having fun - go do something that is fun to you.<br>
